obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (38029)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38029&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Motor Vehicles`
  line `Taxation Act, 1962.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the ^2[Administrator] may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st April, 1963, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1254 (E), dated 18th September, 1962, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3 (i).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 2, for "Chief Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (38030)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38030&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires--`
  line
  line `^1[1(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of Delhi appointed by the President under article`
  line `239 of the Constitution;]`
  line
  line `(b) "Delhi" means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "quarter" means a period of three months commencing on the first day of April, the first day`
  line `of July, the first day of October or the first day of January in each year;`
  line
  line `(e) "registered owner" means the person in whose name a motor vehicle is registered under the`
  line `Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939);`
  line
  line `(f) "tax" means the tax levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "taxation authority" means any person or authority appointed by the ^2[Administrator] by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette to exercise the powers and perform the duties conferred or`
  line `imposed upon a taxation authority by or under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "token" means a ticket to be displayed on a motor vehicle as an indication that the tax has`
  line `been duly paid or that no tax is payable;`
  line
  line `(i) "year" means the financial year;`
  line
  line `(j) all words and expressions used, but not defined in this Act, and defined in the Motor Vehicles`
  line `Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 2, for "Chief Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (38031)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Levy of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38031&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, on and from the commencement of`
  line `the Delhi Motor Vehicles Taxation (Amendment) Act, 1989, there shall be levied and collected on--`
  line
  line `(a) all motor vehicles described in column (1) of Part A of Schedule I and used or kept for use in`
  line `Delhi, a tax at the rate specified in the corresponding entry in column (2) of the said Part;`
  line
  line `(b) all motor vehicles described in column (1) of Part B of Schedule I and used or kept for use in`
  line Delhi--
  line
  line `(i) on their first registration in Delhi, a one time tax at the amount specified in the`
  line `corresponding entry in column (2) of the said Part;`
  line
  line `(ii) the same having been earlier registered in Delhi or in any other State, then having regard`
  line `to the month of their first registration in Delhi or, as the case may be, in that other State, a one`
  line `time tax at the amount specified in the respective columns (3) to (14) of Part C of Schedule I:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such motor vehicles are more than ten years old from the date of their first`
  line `registration, the owners thereof shall present the registration certificates of such motor vehicles to the`
  line `taxation authority for an endorsement therein to the effect that the motor vehicles are more than ten years`
  line `old and their use or keeping for use in Delhi do not attract any tax.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, increase from time to time, the`
  line `rate specified in Schedule I in relation to any motor vehicles:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rate as so increased shall in no case exceed the rate as so specified by more than`
  line `twenty-five per cent. thereof:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that any such increase shall not apply in respect of a motor vehicle specified in`
  line `Part B of Schedule I on which one time tax has been levied and collected.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 1989, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-2-1990).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso added by Act 25 of 1989, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (38032)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Declaration and payment of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clauses (a), (b) and (c) (w.e.f. 1-2-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38032&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered owner or person having possession or`
  line `control of a motor vehicle used or kept for use in Delhi shall fill up and sign a declaration in the`
  line `prescribed form stating the prescribed particulars and shall deliver the same to the taxation authority`
  line `within the prescribed time.`
  line
  line `(2) The tax to which a registered owner or person having possession or control of a motor vehicle`
  line `appears by such declaration to be liable under section 3 shall be paid by him,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) where such vehicle is described in Part A of Schedule I,--`
  line
  line `(i) for a year at the rate specified in the corresponding entry in column (2) thereof (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the annual rate); or`
  line
  line `(ii) for one or more quarters, at one-fourth of the annual rate for each quarter; or`
  line
  line `(iii) for any period less than a quarter expiring on the last day of the quarter, at one-twelfth of`
  line `the annual rate for each complete month or part thereof included in such period; or`
  line
  line `(b) where such vehicle is described in Part B of Schedule I, a one time tax at the amount specified`
  line `in the corresponding entry in column (2) in the said Part or, as the case may be, the amount specified`
  line `in the respective columns in Part C.]`
  line
  line `(3) The tax shall be paid within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) In calculating the tax due for any period less than one year, fraction of a rupee shall be counted as`
  line `a rupee.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (38033)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Issue of token.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38033&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person pays the amount of tax leviable under section 3 in respect of`
  line `any motor vehicle or proves to the satisfaction of the taxation authority that no such tax is payable in`
  line `respect of such vehicle, the taxation authority shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) issue to such person a token in the prescribed form specifying therein the period for which`
  line `such tax has been paid or that no such tax is payable, and`
  line
  line `(b) specify in the certificate of registration granted in respect of the vehicle under the Motor`
  line `Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939), or in the case of vehicles not registered under that Act, in a certificate`
  line `in such form as may be prescribed, that the tax has been paid for the period specified under clause (a)`
  line `or that no tax is payable in respect of that vehicle, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) No motor vehicle liable to tax under this Act shall be used or kept for use in Delhi unless the`
  line `registered owner or the person having possession or control of such vehicle has obtained a valid token in`
  line `respect of that vehicle, and that token is displayed on the vehicle in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (38053)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Additional declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38053&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a motor vehicle used or kept for use in Delhi is altered or is`
  line `proposed to be used in such manner as to render the registered owner or the person who has possession or`
  line `control of such vehicle liable to the payment of additional tax under section 7, such owner or person shall`
  line `fill up, sign and deliver in the manner provided in sub-section (2), an additional declaration and shall,`
  line `along with such additional declaration (accompanied by the certificate of registration in respect of such`
  line `motor vehicle), pay to the taxation authority an additional tax payable under that section which he appears`
  line `by such additional declaration to be liable to pay in respect of such vehicle.`
  line
  line `(2) The additional declaration shall be in the prescribed form containing the prescribed particulars and`
  line `shall be delivered to the taxation authority after being duly filled up and signed within the prescribed`
  line `time. The additional declaration shall indicate clearly also the nature of alteration made in the motor`
  line `vehicle or, as the case may be, the altered use to which the vehicle is proposed to be put.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of the additional tax under sub-section (1), the taxation authority shall issue to the`
  line `registered owner or the person who has possession or control of the vehicle, a fresh token in place of the`
  line `original token and shall cause an entry of such payment to be made in the certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (38054)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Liability for additional tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38054&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `When any motor vehicle in respect of which a tax for any period is`
  line `payable or has been paid, is altered during such period, or proposed to be used during such period in such`
  line `manner as to cause the vehicle to become a vehicle in respect of which a higher rate of tax is payable, the`
  line `registered owner or the person who has possession or control of the vehicle, shall, in addition to the tax, if`
  line `any, due from him for that period, be liable to pay for the unexpired portion of such period since the`
  line `vehicle is altered or proposed to be used, an additional tax of a sum equal to the difference between the`
  line `amount of tax payable for such unexpired portion at the higher rate and the rate at which the tax was`
  line `payable or paid before the alteration or use of the vehicle for that portion; and until such additional tax`
  line `has been paid, the taxation authority shall not grant a fresh token in respect of the vehicle so altered or`
  line `proposed to be so used.`
  line
  line `Explanation--In calculating the unexpired portion under this section any broken period in a month`
  line `shall be considered as a full month.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (38035)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Production of certificate of insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38035&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Every registered owner or person having possession or`
  line `control of a motor vehicle shall, at the time of making payment of the tax, produce before the taxation`
  line `authority a valid certificate of insurance in respect of the vehicle complying with the requirements of`
  line `Chapter VIII of the Motor Vehicles Act, 1939 (4 of 1939).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (38055)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Liability to pay arrears of tax of person succeeding to the ownership, possession or control of motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38055&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the tax leviable in respect of any motor vehicle remains unpaid by any person`
  line `liable for payment thereof and such person before having paid the tax has transferred the ownership of`
  line `such vehicle or has ceased to be in possession or control of such vehicle, the person to whom the`
  line `ownership of the vehicle has been transferred or the person who has possession or control of such vehicle`
  line `shall be liable to pay the said tax to the taxation authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the liability to pay the said tax of the`
  line `person who has transferred the ownership or has ceased to be in possession or control of such vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (38037)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Refund of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 1989, s. 4, for section 10 (w.e.f. 1-2-1990).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38037&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Refund of tax.--(1) When any person who has paid the tax in respect of a motor vehicle`
  line `produces before the taxation authority a certificate signed by the registering authority stating that the tax`
  line `token and the certificate of registration issued in respect of such vehicle have been surrendered on the`
  line `date specified by the registering authority in his certificate, such person shall, on an application made in`
  line `that behalf to the taxation authority and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, be entitled to a`
  line refund,--
  line
  line `(a) in a case where payment of tax has been made in accordance with clause (a) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 4, for each complete month of the period for which such tax has been paid and which is`
  line `unexpired on the date on which the tax token and the certificate of registration were surrendered, of`
  line `an amount equal to one-twelfth of the annual tax payable in respect of such vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where payment of tax has been made in accordance with clause (b) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 4, at the rates specified in Schedule IA.`
  line
  line `(2) When any person has paid the tax in respect of a motor vehicle and the vehicle is removed outside`
  line `Delhi before the expiry of the period for which the tax has been paid and taxed in another State or the`
  line `registration of such vehicle is cancelled before the expiry of the period for which the tax has been paid,`
  line `such person shall, on an application made in that behalf to the taxation authority and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed, be entitled to a refund,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where payment of tax has been made in accordance with clause (a) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 4, for each complete month of the period for which such tax has been paid, and during`
  line `which the vehicle was removed from Delhi or such vehicle's registration is cancelled, of an amount`
  line `equal to one-twelfth of the annual tax payable in respect of such vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where payment of tax has been made in accordance with clause (b) of sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 4, at the rates specified in Schedule IB.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the rates of tax leviable under Part B of Schedule I are increased by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette under sub-section (2) of section 3, the Administrator may, from time to time, by the same`
  line `notification or by a separate notification in the Official Gazette, correspondingly increase the rates of`
  line `refund payable under this section and the refund of tax payable in respect of the vehicles registered on or`
  line `after the date of such notification shall be at such increased rates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (38038)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Penalty payable when tax not paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38038&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `When any registered owner or any person who has`
  line `possession or control of any motor vehicle used or kept for use in Delhi is in default in making a payment`
  line `of the tax the taxation authority may direct that, in addition to the amount of arrears, a sum not exceeding`
  line `the annual tax payable in respect of such vehicle shall be recovered from him by way of penalty:`
  line
  line `Provided that before giving any such direction the registered owner or such person shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (38039)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Arrears of tax and penalty recoverable as arrears of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38039&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any tax due and not`
  line `paid as provided for by or under this Act and any sum directed to be recovered by way of penalty under`
  line `section 11 shall be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) The motor vehicle in respect of which the tax is due or in respect of which any sum has been`
  line `directed to be recovered as penalty under section 11, or its accessories may be distrained and sold in`
  line `pursuance of this section whether or not such vehicle or accessories is or are in the possession or control`
  line `of the person liable to pay the tax or penalty.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (38040)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Exemptions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 2, for "Chief Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38040&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the registered owner or the person having possession or control of a`
  line `motor vehicle is an agriculturist and that motor vehicle has been designed for agricultural operations and`
  line `is used solely for such operations in relation to his own land then, that vehicle shall be exempt from the`
  line `payment of the tax.`
  line
  line `Explanations.--For the purposes of this sub-section the expression "agricultural operations"`
  line includes,--
  line
  line `(i) tilling, sowing, harvesting, crushing of any agricultural produce or any other similar operation`
  line `carried out for the purpose of agriculture;`
  line
  line `(ii) transport of manure, seeds, insecticides and other like articles required for work in the land`
  line `from the market to the land; and`
  line
  line `(iii) transport of any agricultural produce from the land to the place of storage or from the place`
  line `of storage to the market.`
  line
  line `(2) When the registered owner or the person having possession or control of a motor vehicle has`
  line `given previous intimation in writing to the taxation authority that the motor vehicle would not be used in`
  line `any public place for a particular period, being not less than one month, and deposits the certificate of`
  line `registration of such motor vehicle with the taxation authority and obtains an acknowledgement therefor`
  line `from that authority, he shall be exempt from the payment of the tax for that period.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the ^1[Administrator] is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest so`
  line `to do, he may, by notification in the Official Gazette, and subject to such conditions as he may specify in`
  line `the notification, exempt either totally or partially any class of motor vehicles other than those falling`
  line `under sub-section (1) or any motor vehicles belonging to any class of persons from the payment of the`
  line tax.
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (38041)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Reduction of tax in cases of certain motor vehicles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38041&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Where the registered owner of a motor`
  line `vehicle used or kept for use in Delhi is a co-operative society registered under any law relating to`
  line `co-operative societies for the time being in force, the tax payable in respect of that motor vehicle shall be`
  line `one half of the rates specified in Schedule I, if the taxation authority is satisfied, after such enquiry as it`
  line `deems fit that,--`
  line
  line `(i) the co-operative society is solely enagaged in the business of transport of goods or passengers`
  line `or both from one place to another in motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(ii) at least seventy-five per cent. of the members of the co-operative society are its employees;`
  line
  line `(iii) at least fifty per cent. of the members of the co-operative society are not related to each other;`
  line and
  line
  line `(iv) the motor vehicle is used or kept for use exclusively for the purpose of the co-operative`
  line society.
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of this section a member shall be deemed to be related to any other`
  line `member if that member is the husband, wife, brother or sister or any lineal ascendant or descendant of`
  line `that other member.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (38042)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Effect of payment of tax in other States with respect to motor vehicles brought into Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38042&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Where in respect of a motor vehicle the tax payable under the law relating to taxation on motor vehicles`
  line `in force in any State has been paid in that State for any period and that motor vehicle is brought into Delhi`
  line `for use during that period, then,--`
  line
  line `(i) no tax under this Act shall be payable in respect of that motor vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the token issued in that State in respect of that motor vehicle shall be deemed to be a token`
  line `issued under this Act,`
  line
  line `for such period or for a period of ninety days from the date on which the motor vehicle is brought into`
  line `Delhi, whichever is shorter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered owner or the person having possession or control of the motor vehicle`
  line `complies with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (38043)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38043&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is aggrieved by any order or direction of the taxation authority`
  line `may file an appeal before such person or authority, in such manner, within such time and on payment of`
  line `such fees, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The appeal shall be heard and decided in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every decision on such appeal shall be final and shall not be called in question in any court of`
  line law.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (38044)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers of police officers and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38044&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any police officer in uniform, not below the rank`
  line `of Sub-Inspector or any other officer prescribed in this behalf may--`
  line
  line `(a) enter at any time between sunrise and sunset any premises where he has reason to believe that`
  line `a motor vehicle is kept, or,`
  line
  line `(b) require the driver of any motor vehicle in any public place to stop such vehicle and cause it to`
  line `remain stationary so long as may reasonably be necessary,`
  line
  line `for the purpose of satisfying himself that the amount of the tax in respect of such vehicle, has been paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (38045)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Penalty for incomplete and untrue declaration, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38045&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) delivers in respect of a motor vehicle a declaration or additional declaration wherein the`
  line `particulars required by or under this Act to be therein set forth are not fully and truly stated, or`
  line
  line `(b) obstructs any officer in the exercise of the powers conferred by clause (a) of section 17 or`
  line `fails to stop the motor vehicle when required to do so by such officer under clause (b) of that section,`
  line
  line `shall on conviction be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) with fine which may extend to a sum equal to the annual tax payable in respect of such`
  line `vehicle; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the event of such person having been previously convicted of an offence under this section,`
  line `with fine which may extend to a sum equal to twice the annual tax payable in respect of such vehicle.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (38046)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Other penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38046&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder other than those punishable under section 18 shall on conviction be punishable with fine which`
  line `may extend to one hundred rupees and in the event of such person having been previously convicted of an`
  line `offence under this section, with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (38047)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Utilization of the proceeds of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1965, s. 2, for section 20 (w.e.f. 27-11-1965).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38047&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Utilization of the proceeds of tax.--The proceeds of the tax collected under this Act (which`
  line `shall form part of the Consolidated Fund of India) reduced by the cost of collection as determined by the`
  line `Central Government shall, if Parliament by appropriation made by law in this behalf so provides, be paid`
  line to,--
  line
  line `(i) the Municipal Corporation of Delhi established under section 3 of the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(ii) the New Delhi Municipal Committee established under section 11 of the Punjab Municipal`
  line `Act, 1911 (Punjab Act 3 of 1911), as extended to Delhi; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the Cantonment Board, Delhi, constituted under the Cantonments Act, 1924 (2 of 1924),`
  line
  line `for the performance of their respective functions under the said Acts and the payment shall be made in`
  line `such proportion as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (38048)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38048&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No court inferior to that of a magistrate of the second class shall try an`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (38049)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Protection for bona fide acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38049&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution, suit or other proceedings, shall lie against the`
  line `taxation authority or any other authority for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (38050)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38050&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Administrator] may, subject to the condition of previous`
  line `publication, make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision,`
  line `the ^1[Administrator] may make rules for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, the tax shall be paid;`
  line
  line `(b) the form of declaration and additional declaration, particulars to be stated therein and the time`
  line `within which the declaration or additional declaration shall be delivered under section 4 or section 6,`
  line `as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) the form of the tax token and the manner in which the tax token shall be displayed in the`
  line `motor vehicle under section 5;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which refund of tax may be allowed under section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) the authority before which, the manner in which, the time within which and the fee on`
  line `payment of which, an appeal may be filed and the manner in which such appeal shall be heard and`
  line `decided under section 16;`
  line
  line `(f) the issue of duplicate tokens and of certified copies of the records of the taxation authority and`
  line `the fees chargeable therefor;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made under this section and every notification issued under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 3 ^3[and sub-section (3) of section 10] shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made or issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or notification, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made or the`
  line `notification should not be issued, the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 2, for "Chief Commissioner" (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 1983, s. 5, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-12-1983).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 25 of 1989, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-2-1990)`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (38051)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Repeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38051&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the Acts specified in Schedule II shall`
  line `stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of the said Acts by sub-section (1) shall not affect,--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of the said Acts or anything duly done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or right conferred, accrued or incurred under any of the said`
  line `Acts; or`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed against`
  line `any of the said Acts;`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceedings or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if the said Acts had not been repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (2) and notwithstanding the repeal of the Punjab`
  line `Motor Vehicles Taxation Act, 1924 (Punjab Act 4 of 1924), as extended to Delhi,--`
  line
  line `(i) every declaration delivered under that Act in respect of any motor vehicle shall be deemed to`
  line `be a declaration delivered under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) every token issued under that Act and valid immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, shall continue to be valid after such commencement for the unexpired portion of the period for`
  line `which it has been issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (38052)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Amendment of section 184, Act 66 of 1957.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320&sectionId=38052&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_7_7_00001_196257_1517807317320
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `In the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957,`
  line `for section 184, the following section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"184. Central Government to pay proceeds of entertainment and betting taxes to`
  line `Corporation.--The proceeds of the entertainment and betting taxes collected in Delhi under the`
  line `provisions, of the U. P. Entertainment and Betting Tax Act, 1937 (U.P. Act 8 of 1937), as extended to`
  line `Delhi (which shall form part of the Consolidated Fund of India) reduced by the cost of collection as`
  line `determined by the Central Government shall, if Parliament by appropriation made by law in this`
  line `behalf so provides, be paid to the Corporation for the performance of its functions under this Act.".`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
